The paper deals with generating realistic labeled masses in bio-image computing fields using deep learning. This involves visual feature processing in latent space, which is a common technique used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions computer-aided detection and diagnosis, which falls under medical imaging (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses generative models, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
